\f0\fs24 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Love this one. It has a mechanic the Pivot Simulator doesn't: the clock is the enemy AND a liar. Here's the full treatment:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Core loop
\f0\b0 \
A live transcript scrolls in real time. Coworkers speak, line by line, like a chat feed. You watch the meeting happen and react. The game is attention management: stay engaged enough to respond correctly when danger comes, but engagement drains your Focus, and Focus is what you need to survive the whole thing.\

\f1\b The signature mechanic: the timer goes up
\f0\b0 \
The meeting is scheduled for 30 minutes. The timer can and will exceed it. The Rambler adds time. "Quick question" adds 4 minutes, always. "One more thing" as people are saying goodbye adds 6. Watching 30:00 become 34:00 while you're powerless is the emotional core of the game. Your special moves are the only way to claw time back, but each costs social capital. That's the central trade: suffer silently or intervene and be perceived.\

