\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Nod QTEs.
\f0\b0  Prompts appear on a timing window when someone makes a point. Nod on time: small Visibility maintenance, cheap and safe. Miss: nothing. Nod at the WRONG moment: disaster ("You nodded while Karen announced the reorg. HR has noted your enthusiasm."). Occasionally the game baits you with a nod prompt during bad news.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Called-on quizzes.
\f0\b0  "Thoughts, [you]?" with a 6-second timer and 3 response options. Here's the hook: the correct answer depends on what was actually said in the last 30 seconds of transcript. If you were zoned out recovering Focus, you weren't reading, and the options are all coin flips. The game rewards actually skimming the fake meeting content, which is the joke eating itself.\
\ls2\ilvl0
